  "original_title": "Sri Lanka T-bill rates up in secondary market; guidance peg steady",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka T-bill rates up in secondary market; guidance peg steady",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013Yields in risk free treasury bills rates at the secondary market rose on Wednesday while Sri Lanka\u2019s guidance peg on interbank spot trading remained steady, dealers said.",
        "The three months\u2019 bill yield closed at 27.00/28.00 percent, up from Tuesday\u2019s close at 26.30/27.30 percent.",
        "The One-year bill closed at 28.30/29.30 percent, up from 28.00/29.00 percent in the last close.",
        "Sri Lanka raised 85 billion rupees of Treasury bills with yields fell across maturities and most of the money taken from 3-month bills, data from the state debt office showed.",
        "A guidance peg announced by Sri Lanka\u2019s central bank for interbank transactions was steady at 361.00 rupees, unchanged from the previous day.",
        "Commercial banks offered dollars for telegraphic transfers at rates between 368.00 and 370.00 for small transactions on July 27, data showed.",
        "Banks offered to buy inward remittances at 358.00 -359.00 rupees. (Colombo/July 27/2022)"
      ],
